**Damage Report:**

**Vehicle Make/Model:** Not specified (only the rear portion of the vehicle is visible).

**Location of Damage:** The damage appears to be located on the rear quarter panel of the vehicle.

**Type of Damage:**
- **Scratches and Dents:** There are noticeable scratches and dents on the rear quarter panel. The damage seems to be concentrated around the area where the rear door meets the body of the car.
- **Paint Damage:** The paint has been chipped and scratched, indicating that the surface has been compromised.
- **Panel Distortion:** The panel itself appears to have some distortion, suggesting that the metal may have been bent or compressed.

**Additional Notes:**
- The damage looks like it could have been caused by a minor collision or impact.
- The extent of the damage suggests that the vehicle may need repairs to restore its original condition.

**Recommendation:**
- Inspect the rest of the vehicle for any additional damage.
- Schedule an appointment with a repair shop to assess the full extent of the damage and provide an estimate for repairs.

If you need further information or have more details about the vehicle, please provide them so I can assist you better.
